 Peddie - Peddie police are investigating a fire that gutted eight shops early on Tuesday morning. "Peddie Vispol members, who were conducting patrols in the town noticed smoke from Alex, a foreigner-owned shop, which is adjacent to Peddie Spar," said police spokesperson, Captain Khaya Tonjeni. "The fire spread rapidly affected eight shops in a short time." He said that the Amathole District dispatched Komga fire fighters to the scene, who tried to extinguish the fire. "A total of eight buildings were affected by the fire - namely a supermarket, saloon and six foreign-owned shops, of which three of them were Hardware shops." Capt Tonjeni said that the cause of the fire is still to be determined. "Emergency,firefighters and all roleplayers are still at the scene," he said. "Damage by the fire is unknown and yet to be estimated. "The investigation will guide the police next action regarding this incident." Follow more RNEWS articles, subscribe to our YouTube channel and for breaking news LIKE us on Facebook. For news on the Western Cape click here. For great savings on life’s little pleasures visit Bargain Buys!  Know somebody who is getting married, Wedding and Function can assist.  Have kids, then you need to visit Kids Connection. Enjoy food and travel, then visit Home Food and Travel. Need assistance with an online presence, visit Agency One. 